    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Offered is an investment-grade 1994 Mazda RX-7 (FD), showcasing a meticulously maintained 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary engine. This example retains its factory-spec vacuum line routing and displays optimal compression across all rotor faces. The chassis features a perfect 50/50 weight distribution, supported by an unmolested four-wheel double-wishbone suspension and a Torsen limited-slip differential for precise power delivery. Finished in its original Montego Blue, the exterior remains showroom-fresh with zero oxidation or clear coat failure. The interior features pristine plastics and supple leather, free from the typical sun-induced warping. Mechanically sound with a recent overhaul of the cooling system and vacuum viton lines, this RX-7 represents a rare opportunity for the discerning collector seeking peak performance and structural integrity.",
      "price": 43500.0,
